    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="57"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d57">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Staff of the Army</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_MGC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marshall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LWD1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d57fn1">This memorandum bears in the upper
                        right-hand corner a penciled notation, in <persName corresp="#p_LWD1"
                            >Leahy</persName>’s handwriting, which appears to read: “Tell <persName
                            corresp="#p_MGC1">Marshall</persName> (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) if
                            <persName corresp="#p_SIV1">Stalin</persName> comes to Basra (<hi
                            rend="italic">b</hi>) if he does not come to conf &amp; sends Molitof to
                        a meeting in Cairo msg [message] to be sent immed[iately] after <gloss
                            target="#t_UJ1">U J.</gloss> is heard from”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-25">25 October
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for Admiral <persName corresp="#p_LWD1"
                            >Leahy</persName>
                    </hi>:</p>
                <p>The following is a first trial at a draft of a message regarding the subject of
                    Russian participation in the Combined Chiefs of Staff conferences. You will
                    recall that the other day I was opposed to a formal joining up by the Russians
                    with our Chiefs of Staff organization, first, because I felt certain the
                    Russians would feel that we were endeavoring to penetrate their strategical and
                    operational plans, and further, that it would be next to impossible to reach
                    final decisions with such a variegated group. My view is to make a small
                    beginning, and very definitely on the basis that we are not asking for anything
                    from the Russians in the way of information but are offering them virtually a
                    complete insight into all of our strategical and logistical doings.</p>
                <p>The following is the proposed message from the President to the Prime
                    Minister:</p>
                <p>[The proposed message which follows at this point was sent as <persName
                        corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>’s telegram 397, October 26, 1943, to
                        <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>, printed <hi rend="italic"
                        >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_42">p. 42</ref>, with the changes indicated in
                    footnotes 2 and 3.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGC1">G C <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chief of Staff</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>King should have a shot at this before final consideration. G. C. M.<note
                            n="2" xml:id="d57fn2">The postscript was handwritten.</note>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
